00:52:29,603 --> 00:52:30,604
Hey, Han-young.

780
00:52:31,188 --> 00:52:32,523
Lee Chang-hyo's gone.

781
00:52:50,541 --> 00:52:51,876
I was a bit too late.

782
00:53:01,302 --> 00:53:02,469
Director Lee Chang-hyo of Hanguk Hospital

783
00:53:02,553 --> 00:53:04,805
who was under the allegation
that he gave false diagnoses

784
00:53:04,889 --> 00:53:06,891
to help men get an exemption
from conscription

785
00:53:06,974 --> 00:53:08,475
jumped off a building and died.

786
00:53:08,934 --> 00:53:11,812
He is suspected to have taken his own life

787
00:53:11,896 --> 00:53:14,523
under great pressure
before being summoned by the prosecution.

788
00:53:14,940 --> 00:53:16,483
According to the prosecution

789
00:53:16,567 --> 00:53:19,195
the confiscated flash drive had
the same list

790
00:53:19,278 --> 00:53:21,530
as the one in the book of draft dodgers.

791
00:53:22,198 --> 00:53:23,908
Under the speculation

792
00:53:23,991 --> 00:53:26,285
that there was someone
who acted as an informant

793
00:53:26,368 --> 00:53:28,495
the prosecution planned
to extend the investigation

794
00:53:28,579 --> 00:53:30,164
but with Director Lee's death

795
00:53:30,247 --> 00:53:32,750
further investigation may not continue.

796
00:53:33,751 --> 00:53:35,669
Sin-jin chopped his tail off.

797
00:53:36,587 --> 00:53:38,297
Because Director Lee's words could tell

798
00:53:38,380 --> 00:53:40,716
his biggest weaknesses.

799
00:53:50,142 --> 00:53:51,936
I can't ask a prosecutor to dig

800
00:53:52,019 --> 00:53:53,896
into a Ministry of Justice candidate.

801
00:54:09,411 --> 00:54:10,746
Hey, kid!

802
00:54:11,705 --> 00:54:13,374
Where do you think you're going?

803
00:54:18,212 --> 00:54:20,297
You said you'd take all the food
past the best-before date.

804
00:54:20,756 --> 00:54:21,799
I didn't mean

805
00:54:22,383 --> 00:54:23,467
every day.

806
00:54:25,010 --> 00:54:26,011
Come every day.

807
00:54:30,724 --> 00:54:31,725
Huh?

808
00:54:33,435 --> 00:54:34,436
Never mind.

809
00:54:35,104 --> 00:54:36,105
Here.

810
00:54:41,026 --> 00:54:42,403
Hey, Han-young.

811
00:54:46,282 --> 00:54:47,283
Yeah.

812
00:54:48,450 --> 00:54:50,244
Can you dig into someone's background?

813
00:54:50,661 --> 00:54:51,704
Who is it?

814
00:54:52,371 --> 00:54:55,040
Woo Gyo-hun. He's an assemblyman.
Can you do it?

815
00:54:55,124 --> 00:54:56,709
What? Woo...

816
00:54:59,211 --> 00:55:01,797
WOO GYO-HUN, NOMINATED
AS THE NEXT MINISTER OF JUSTICE

817
00:55:05,092 --> 00:55:06,260
Of course!

818
00:55:06,343 --> 00:55:08,887
You know me. I can do anything.

819
00:55:09,388 --> 00:55:11,140
I'll look into him and let you know.

820
00:55:19,690 --> 00:55:21,525
My gosh, seriously.

821
00:55:21,608 --> 00:55:24,194
Babe, shouldn't you go to another country?

822
00:55:24,278 --> 00:55:25,904
Before they assign a travel ban?

823
00:55:25,988 --> 00:55:28,365
Come on, babe.

824
00:55:28,449 --> 00:55:30,117
My father is a Justice.

825
00:55:30,200 --> 00:55:32,953
We live in Korea.
They don't arrest everyone

826
00:55:33,037 --> 00:55:34,580
just because they're on the list.

827
00:55:35,539 --> 00:55:36,540
That's true.

828
00:55:36,623 --> 00:55:39,293
Korea is heaven for the rich
with the right connections.

829
00:55:39,376 --> 00:55:41,337
That's why money and connections are

830
00:55:41,462 --> 00:55:44,131
basically God here.

831
00:55:50,554 --> 00:55:51,555
Who the hell are you?

832
00:55:54,641 --> 00:55:57,603
Park Cheol-woo, a prosecutor of Korea.

833
00:55:57,686 --> 00:55:58,687
Mr. Kim Jeong-gyun

834
00:55:58,771 --> 00:56:01,690
you're under emergency arrest
for violating the Military Service Act.

835
00:56:01,774 --> 00:56:04,651
You have the right to an attorney
and the right to remain silent.

836
00:56:04,735 --> 00:56:05,736
You heard me, right?

837
00:56:05,819 --> 00:56:08,030
Honestly, you're embarrassing me!

838
00:56:09,031 --> 00:56:11,825
You bastards, you know who my father is?

839
00:56:11,909 --> 00:56:14,870
He's the freaking Justice!

840
00:56:14,953 --> 00:56:16,872
Where are you guys from?

841
00:56:19,583 --> 00:56:20,584
Just wait and see.

842
00:56:22,378 --> 00:56:23,462
Babe.

843
00:56:23,837 --> 00:56:24,963
What? Hold on.

844
00:56:26,006 --> 00:56:27,674
- Look over there.
- What?

845
00:56:27,758 --> 00:56:29,301
Just look at that!

846
00:56:34,723 --> 00:56:37,559
JUSTICE KIM JUN-MAN ARRESTED
FOR HIS SON'S ALLEGED DRAFT DODGING

847
00:56:40,312 --> 00:56:41,355
Father?

848
00:56:44,691 --> 00:56:46,402
You still want to know where I'm from?

849
00:56:48,821 --> 00:56:51,365
My, my.

850
00:56:52,324 --> 00:56:55,077
It can't get more embarrassing than this.

851
00:56:55,744 --> 00:56:56,787
EOM JUN-HO
PROSECUTOR GENERAL

852
00:56:56,870 --> 00:56:58,080
Yi-seok, that damn bastard.

853
00:56:58,163 --> 00:57:01,125
He should've just stayed quiet
at the Chungnam Court until the end

854
00:57:01,208 --> 00:57:03,210
and enjoyed his authority there.

855
00:57:04,086 --> 00:57:07,506
Can't believe he used some newbie
to get everyone like this.

856
00:57:08,215 --> 00:57:09,258
Don't you agree?

857
00:57:09,341 --> 00:57:11,552
Your son will be investigated separately.

858
00:57:15,264 --> 00:57:16,473
You're

859
00:57:17,266 --> 00:57:18,642
two classes after me, yeah?

860
00:57:20,102 --> 00:57:22,980
Everyone's a former official
once our badges come off.

861
00:57:24,398 --> 00:57:26,775
You have to earn what you can
while you serve the nation

862
00:57:26,859 --> 00:57:28,193
and still have your position.

863
00:57:28,610 --> 00:57:29,820
So

864
00:57:30,195 --> 00:57:33,282
take good care of your colleagues,
old and young, while you have the power.

865
00:57:33,907 --> 00:57:35,617
If you mess with the Judiciary

866
00:57:35,826 --> 00:57:37,953
even your former title will mean nothing.

867
00:57:40,581 --> 00:57:41,665
You understand

868
00:57:42,249 --> 00:57:43,417
what I mean?

869
00:57:46,086 --> 00:57:49,631
The Senior Presidential Economic Advisor
will join us soon

870
00:57:50,132 --> 00:57:52,050
for draft dodging charges, too.

871
00:57:59,975 --> 00:58:01,685
Have a good time, and get home safely.

872
00:58:02,561 --> 00:58:03,687
Treat him well.

873
00:58:04,354 --> 00:58:05,689
Don't miss a single detail.

874
00:58:05,772 --> 00:58:06,857
Yes, sir.

875
00:58:09,526 --> 00:58:10,527
Mr. Kim

876
00:58:11,445 --> 00:58:14,907
serving in the military is
an honorable responsibility

877
00:58:14,990 --> 00:58:16,992
that comes before any duty
of any officials.

878
00:58:20,913 --> 00:58:22,164
Hey!

879
00:58:24,374 --> 00:58:27,377
PROSECUTOR GENERAL EOM JUN-HO

880
00:58:27,711 --> 00:58:29,379
I didn't know

881
00:58:30,088 --> 00:58:31,798
we had another brat like Yi-seok here.

882
00:58:38,639 --> 00:58:39,932
Damn it.

883
00:58:46,313 --> 00:58:48,023
JUSTICE IS DEAD

884
00:58:48,607 --> 00:58:50,234
PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

885
00:58:50,317 --> 00:58:52,486
LIKE FATHER, LIKE SON
OUR COUNTRY IS FALLING APART!

886
00:58:54,363 --> 00:58:57,157
The trial for the case of draft dodging
went at an unprecedented speed

887
00:58:57,324 --> 00:59:00,077
even for the Senior Economic Advisor,
who resisted until the end.

888
00:59:02,246 --> 00:59:03,914
The Chief Justice resigned

889
00:59:03,997 --> 00:59:05,457
and with the draft dodging scandal

890
00:59:05,541 --> 00:59:08,377
thinking that it'd lost
the nation's trust and respect

891
00:59:08,460 --> 00:59:11,004
the President's Office screwed
with the Judiciary big time.

892
00:59:12,673 --> 00:59:13,674
JUSTICE CANNOT BE RESTORED
WITHOUT FAIR CONSCRIPTION RULES!

893
00:59:14,508 --> 00:59:15,509
Breaking news.

894
00:59:15,592 --> 00:59:18,470
The Blue House nominated Jeon Heung-woo
of the Jeju District Court

895
00:59:18,554 --> 00:59:21,431
as the next Chief Justice.

896
00:59:21,932 --> 00:59:23,850
- Mr. Jeon has been extraordinary...
- First

897
00:59:23,934 --> 00:59:25,811
I will ensure

898
00:59:25,894 --> 00:59:27,688
that integrity and fairness are

899
00:59:27,771 --> 00:59:29,189
the foundation of the Judiciary.

900
00:59:29,648 --> 00:59:31,441
Trust in the Judiciary begins

901
00:59:31,525 --> 00:59:34,278
with the integrity of every judge.

902
00:59:34,361 --> 00:59:37,531
I will ensure every case is judged
and every word is written fairly

903
00:59:37,614 --> 00:59:41,535
and without being in anyone's favor.

904
00:59:41,910 --> 00:59:42,911
Secondly

905
00:59:43,745 --> 00:59:44,746
I will establish...

906
00:59:44,830 --> 00:59:47,708
Jeon, who graduated from a local college
with an underwhelming career

907
00:59:47,791 --> 00:59:50,544
mercilessly purged people
under the name of reform

908
00:59:50,627 --> 00:59:53,213
as soon as he became the Chief Justice.

909
00:59:54,339 --> 00:59:55,340
And

910
00:59:57,342 --> 00:59:58,468
as I'd expected

911
00:59:58,552 --> 01:00:01,471
Heung-woo took an interest in Yi-seok.

912
01:00:02,848 --> 01:00:06,184
CHUNGNAM DISTRICT COURT

913
01:00:06,518 --> 01:00:07,936
How are you feeling?

914
01:00:08,020 --> 01:00:09,187
All better now?

915
01:00:09,980 --> 01:00:11,189
Yes, I'm all good.

916
01:00:11,940 --> 01:00:12,983
I'm glad.

917
01:00:15,777 --> 01:00:19,323
Chief Justice Jeon called me himself.

918
01:00:19,865 --> 01:00:21,658
He invited me to work at the Seoul Court.

919
01:00:24,661 --> 01:00:25,787
Congratulations.

920
01:00:26,872 --> 01:00:28,248
But I turned him down.

921
01:00:34,963 --> 01:00:35,964
What? Why?

922
01:00:36,256 --> 01:00:37,257
But

923
01:00:39,468 --> 01:00:42,179
he offered two more tickets to Seoul.

924
01:00:44,264 --> 01:00:45,265
So?

925
01:00:47,225 --> 01:00:48,685
Senior Presiding Judge Lim

926
01:00:49,603 --> 01:00:51,188
and Judge Lee

927
01:00:52,397 --> 01:00:54,316
you're coming to Seoul with me.

928
01:01:08,705 --> 01:01:11,375
Oh, gosh! What a relief.

929
01:01:17,297 --> 01:01:18,298
Mr. Kang.

930
01:01:18,590 --> 01:01:19,591
Yes.

931
01:01:21,301 --> 01:01:22,636
Yi-seok is coming to Seoul.

932
01:01:24,846 --> 01:01:27,265
I'm guessing
he'll bring Jeong-sik with him.

933
01:01:27,349 --> 01:01:29,142
And Han-young.

934
01:01:30,268 --> 01:01:31,269
Is that so?

935
01:01:32,896 --> 01:01:36,358
Looks like Han-young
used that damn book to 200%.

936
01:01:37,609 --> 01:01:39,528
Based on how Yi-seok is bringing Han-young

937
01:01:39,611 --> 01:01:42,864
it looks like the draft-dodging scandal
made him trust Han-young more.

938
01:01:43,407 --> 01:01:44,783
Guess so.

939
01:01:45,701 --> 01:01:47,244
How was

940
01:01:48,203 --> 01:01:49,287
Judge Lee?

941
01:01:49,579 --> 01:01:51,123
What do you think I'm like?

942
01:01:52,749 --> 01:01:55,335
You look like someone who can lead me.

943
01:01:56,420 --> 01:01:57,421
He's interesting.

944
01:01:57,879 --> 01:02:00,048
He's as clever as he's ambitious.

945
01:02:01,550 --> 01:02:03,802
It doesn't matter
what Yi-seok thinks of Han-young.

946
01:02:03,885 --> 01:02:05,470
He won't join Yi-seok's side.

947
01:02:07,305 --> 01:02:08,807
Presumptuous of me to say

948
01:02:09,474 --> 01:02:10,892
but isn't it too early to think so?

949
01:02:12,394 --> 01:02:13,937
Yeah, that's presumptuous of you.

950
01:02:15,147 --> 01:02:16,565
I'll keep an eye on him.

951
01:02:16,648 --> 01:02:17,649
Don't worry.

952
01:02:19,443 --> 01:02:21,278
But I wonder

953
01:02:22,612 --> 01:02:24,322
if he'll still do my homework

954
01:02:24,406 --> 01:02:26,616
now that he doesn't need my reward.

955
01:02:27,117 --> 01:02:28,535
Or if he'll just give up.

956
01:02:28,869 --> 01:02:30,454
What do you mean by "homework"?

957
01:02:30,662 --> 01:02:32,164
I told him to get rid of Gyo-hun.

958
01:02:33,081 --> 01:02:35,625
I feel like he'll stab me in the back
if I just let him be.

959
01:02:36,960 --> 01:02:38,503
It's too early to trust Han-young.

960
01:02:38,587 --> 01:02:40,630
Maybe I'll take care of Gyo-hun's case...

961
01:02:42,048 --> 01:02:43,175
Again, presumptuous.

962
01:02:43,967 --> 01:02:45,469
I told you I'd keep an eye on him.

963
01:02:46,887 --> 01:02:49,181
Look more into Han-young instead.

964
01:02:49,264 --> 01:02:51,349
Look into his upbringing

965
01:02:51,433 --> 01:02:53,477
whether he's ever been evicted, and so on.

966
01:02:54,394 --> 01:02:55,687
And

967
01:02:56,146 --> 01:02:58,565
move your guy
from the Chungnam Court to Seoul.

968
01:02:59,357 --> 01:03:01,526
Make him keep watching Yi-seok

969
01:03:01,985 --> 01:03:03,528
and Han-young, too.

970
01:03:06,114 --> 01:03:08,116
Yes, sir.

971
01:03:27,302 --> 01:03:30,597
After the government changed,
and Prosecutor General Eom resigned

972
01:03:30,680 --> 01:03:32,724
his son, who was studying abroad,
visited Korea

973
01:03:32,808 --> 01:03:34,559
and got arrested for drug charges.

974
01:03:35,602 --> 01:03:38,605
And one of the people arrested with him
was Gyo-hun's daughter

975
01:03:38,688 --> 01:03:41,316
- Woo Hui-yeong.
- Ms. Woo, do you admit to your charges?

976
01:03:55,872 --> 01:03:58,375
Why does Sin-jin want to crack down
on Gyo-hun?

977
01:03:59,042 --> 01:04:02,170
Does he know Sin-jin's weak spot?

978
01:04:27,571 --> 01:04:29,573
The real deal begins now.

979
01:04:31,575 --> 01:04:33,243
Let's head to Haenal Law Firm first.

980
01:04:35,328 --> 01:04:38,665
HAENAL LAW FIRM

981
01:04:44,170 --> 01:04:47,215
In my previous life,
I was a slave to Haenal Law Firm.

982
01:04:47,883 --> 01:04:49,676
That, too, was my choice

983
01:04:49,759 --> 01:04:51,469
that only ended in my unjustified death.

984
01:04:54,556 --> 01:04:55,849
Yu Seon-cheol, the Partner at Haenal.

985
01:04:56,683 --> 01:04:58,226
You chose me again

986
01:04:58,310 --> 01:04:59,519
in this life.

987
01:05:00,979 --> 01:05:03,565
But in this life

988
01:05:03,648 --> 01:05:04,649
I decide

989
01:05:05,108 --> 01:05:06,902
your fate.

990
01:05:07,402 --> 01:05:10,947
THE JUDGE RETURNS

991
01:05:35,055 --> 01:05:37,641
The son of the Prosecutor General
is doing drugs in the States.

992
01:05:37,724 --> 01:05:39,643
- So?
- And so is Woo Gyo-hun's daughter.

993
01:05:39,726 --> 01:05:42,145
I think Woo Gyo-hun is mixed up
with the Nammyeon District Mayor.

994
01:05:42,228 --> 01:05:43,396
Looks like he was paid off pretty well.

995
01:05:43,480 --> 01:05:45,190
He was part of the Obok gang.

996
01:05:45,273 --> 01:05:47,359
You can take
the Nammyeon District sinkhole case.

997
01:05:47,442 --> 01:05:50,278
The sinkhole was caused by
faulty water and sewer construction.

998
01:05:50,362 --> 01:05:52,781
Hurry and deal with the guy
who died in the sinkhole first.

999
01:05:53,031 --> 01:05:54,032
He deserved it.

1000
01:05:54,115 --> 01:05:55,700
With the investigation going nowhere

1001
01:05:55,784 --> 01:05:58,161
the victims blamed
the Nammyeon District Office.

1002
01:05:58,244 --> 01:06:01,331
He knows exactly how to use me
to his advantage.

1003
01:06:01,414 --> 01:06:02,540
You need to take action.

1004
01:06:02,624 --> 01:06:05,877
Kang Sin-jin,
you're going to end up in court.

1005
01:06:08,922 --> 01:06:10,924
Subtitles by: Min-sun Kim
